Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Arrange the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{2} in a single layer on a lightly-oiled #baking tray{} and drizzle over a little @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

> TIP: We used 1 tortilla per person but you have enough for 2 each if you're extra hungry.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and remove the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @courgette{1} then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1} in a #colander{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{120%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Add the shallot, pepper and courgette to the pan. Stir and cook until soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic and @Mexican spice{1%tsp} (add less spice if you're not a fan of heat!) and stir well. Cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the mixed beans, @finely chopped tomatoes{1} and @vegetable stock powder{1}. Stir well, then bubble away until the liquid has reduced by half, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> Tip: Add a splash more water if the mixture looks a little dry.

Meanwhile, pop the #tray{} of tortillas on the top shelf of your oven and bake until golden brown and crispy ~{3-5%minutes}. Keep an eye out - you want them to be golden and crispy but not burnt! Once cooked, remove from your oven and lay on some #kitchen paper{} to absorb any excess oil.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out all of the insides into a #bowl{}. Add half the coriander. Halve the @lime{1/2}, squeeze in some lime juice and mash with a #fork{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and keep to one side.

Season the bean mixture to taste with salt and pepper. Lay one tostada on each #plate{} and spoon on the beanie mixture. Add a sprinkle of grated cheese and a dollop of guacamole. Finish with the remaining coriander sprinkled over. Tuck in!

> Step 3 MOD: If you've chosen to add beef mince to your recipe, heat a splash of oil in a frying pan on medium heat at the beginning of the step above. Before adding the veg, add the beef mince and cook until browned, 5-6 mins. Use a wooden spoon to break it up as it cooks. Add the shallot, pepper and courgette to the mince and continue with the recipe as instructed.